objects.name: Fintech AI Deepfake Campaign
objects.description: UNC1069 is using AI-generated deepfake videos of CEOs in Telegram/Zoom meetings to trick cryptocurrency employees into running malicious commands, delivering macOS and Windows backdoors like WAVESHAPER and SUGARLOADER.

objects.content:
Sector: Cryptocurrency, Fintech

Modus operandi:
Social engineering via Telegram, deepfake video calls, ClickFix technique, custom macOS malware families.

objects.name: Operation CYBER GUARDIAN
objects.description: A sophisticated China-linked campaign targeting all four major Singaporean telecommunications operators (Singtel, StarHub, M1, SIMBA) to exfiltrate network-related data and maintain persistence via rootkits.

objects.content:
Sector: Telecommunications

Modus operandi:
Exploitation of zero-day vulnerabilities in firewalls, deployment of passive rootkits, log tampering to evade detection.

objects.name: Muddled Libra vSphere Intrusion
objects.description: Creation of rogue virtual machines within target VMware vSphere environments to conduct reconnaissance, steal Active Directory databases (NTDS.dit), and target Snowflake infrastructure.

objects.content:
Sector: Technology, Cloud Services

Modus operandi:
Social engineering for initial access, rogue VM creation to bypass EDR, use of Chisel for tunneling, and stolen certificates for ticket forging.

objects.abstract: Geopolitical analysis (EN) / European 5G Supply Chain Sovereignty
objects.content:
Sector: Telecommunications

Theme: European 5G Supply Chain Sovereignty

The European Commission is pushing for a revised cybersecurity law to exclude high-risk vendors (Huawei, ZTE) from 18 critical sectors beyond just mobile networks, targeting hybrid threats from Russia and China.

Tags: EU, 5G, Huawei, Sovereignty

objects.name: SSHStalker Linux Botnet
objects.description:
A new Linux botnet leveraging old-school IRC for command-and-control, performing noisy SSH scans and brute-forcing to infect hosts.

Analysis:
SSHStalker prioritizes scale over stealth, utilizing 15-year-old CVEs for privilege escalation and 1-minute cron jobs for persistence.

Recommendations:
- Monitor for unusual outbound IRC connections (port 6667).
- Implement rate-limiting and alerting on SSH brute-force attempts.

objects.name: ZeroDayRAT Commercial Spyware
objects.description:
Advanced commercial spyware for Android and iOS sold on Telegram, offering full remote access including camera/microphone streaming and crypto-theft modules.

Analysis:
This tool represents a democratization of nation-state-level surveillance capabilities, targeting traditional banking and cryptocurrency wallets.

Recommendations:
- Avoid installing applications from untrusted third-party sources or Telegram links.
- Enable mobile threat defense (MTD) solutions on corporate-owned devices.

objects.content: The threat landscape for February 11, 2026, is dominated by the release of the Microsoft Patch Tuesday, which addresses 58 flaws including six actively exploited zero-days. Simultaneously, sophisticated espionage activity from North Korean (UNC1069) and Chinese (UNC3886) actors continues to target high-value sectors like Fintech and Telecommunications. The emergence of 'ZeroDayRAT' as a commercial spyware tool and the discovery of the 'VoidLink' framework indicate a shift toward highly modular and AI-assisted malware development.
